A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 1 of Title 35 of the Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to general
2 provisions regarding law enforcement officers and agencies, so as to provide for certain
3 federal agents to clearly identify themselves while in the performance of their duties; to
4 repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Chapter 1 of Title 35 of the Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to general provisions
8 regarding law enforcement officers and agencies, is amended by adding a new Code section
9 to read as follows:
10 "35-1-24.
11 (a) An agent of United States Immigration and the Customs Enforcement and United
12 States Customs and Border Protection shall, in the performance of his or her duties of
13 either such agency, be required to:
14 (1) Wear a name badge, patch, or other clearly visible insignia that identifies the
15 individual agent; and
16 (2) Wear a uniform that clearly identifies the agency the to which the agent is affiliated.
